WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.000
[Amit Varma]: I have often asked myself the question, what does it mean to be Indian? In recent weeks,

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.920
[Amit Varma]: I have also started asking myself the question, what does it mean to be an Indian citizen?

00:00:15.920 --> 00:00:20.800
[Amit Varma]: We often take it for granted that we are citizens, but citizenship has so many rich shades of

00:00:20.800 --> 00:00:26.360
[Amit Varma]: meaning. On the one hand, it's an administrative category, denoting the basic unit of the population

00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:31.600
[Amit Varma]: of a state. On another, it's a term loaded with virtue and duty, which is why we speak

00:00:31.600 --> 00:00:36.920
[Amit Varma]: of what it means to be a good citizen. The term citizen refers to a legal status. It

00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:42.280
[Amit Varma]: also encloses an understanding of rights that the state is supposed to protect and entitlements

00:00:42.280 --> 00:00:47.840
[Amit Varma]: that it might have granted one. It implies duties that one might have, definitely civic

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:53.840
[Amit Varma]: and perhaps social and political as well. It presupposes a sense of identity and belonging.

00:00:53.840 --> 00:00:58.740
[Amit Varma]: It's a term especially loaded with meaning in modern times, because being a citizen is

00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:03.340
[Amit Varma]: different from being a subject. A handful of centuries ago, we were all subjects of

00:01:03.340 --> 00:01:09.280
[Amit Varma]: some empire or fiefdom or the other. In 1947, when India gained political independence,

00:01:09.280 --> 00:01:15.240
[Amit Varma]: we also gained the right for every Indian to turn from a subject to a citizen, empowered

00:01:15.240 --> 00:01:20.040
[Amit Varma]: at an individual level to be masters of the state. Though I would argue that we still

00:01:20.040 --> 00:01:25.200
[Amit Varma]: have the mentality of subjects. Citizenship is something that we all tend to take for

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:30.720
[Amit Varma]: granted. Although the events of the last weeks have forced many Indians to sit up and re-examine

00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:35.400
[Amit Varma]: what the word means. What does it mean to be an Indian citizen? Although there are articles

00:01:35.400 --> 00:01:41.320
[Amit Varma]: in the constitution and laws passed by Parliament on this subject, one basic truth remains.

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:44.240
[Amit Varma]: Our citizenship is what we make of it.

